### learning points ###
Train-test split evaluates generalization.
Linear regression is supervised learning.
Overfitting means good train but poor test performance.
Accuracy measures classification performance.
Cross-validation improves model evaluation.
** 3/1 notes ***
Unsupervised learning groups data without labels.
K-Means is a popular clustering algorithm.
PCA reduces dimensionality preserving variance.
Spam classification is supervised, unlike clustering or segmentation.
Silhouette Score evaluates clustering quality without labels.

